On 5/24/04 6:16 PM, "George Lyle" <glyle(-at-)pon.type2.com> wrote:

> The electric field inside any conductive shell is zero, so the powder
> won't stick to the metal.

How does that explain that the inside of my plenum is as nicely powdercoated
as the outside?

Physics aside I think there are two problems with doing fuel tanks:

- lack of openings to apply the powder
- paint is porous. POR-15 tank sealer is non porous and cures rock hard.

